def: A sore on the back or hips caused by lying for a long time inbed.

A species of white, unglazed porcelain, in which vases,figures, and groups are formed in miniature. Meat biscuit, analimentary preparation consisting of matters extracted from meat byboiling, or of meat ground fine and combined with flour, so as toform biscuits.
Deck sweepings, refuse of cordage, canvas, etc. Ham. Nav.Encyc.
An amphibian (Amphiuma means) of the order Urodela, found inthe southern United States. See Amphiuma.
Capable of being compassed or accomplished. Burke.
A large squirrel fish (Holocentrus ascensionis) of Florida andthe West Indies.
The under side of the subordinate parts and members ofbuildings, such as staircases, entablatures, archways, cornices, orthe like. See Illust. of Lintel.
A genus of shrubs or small trees, having the foliage coveredwith small silvery scales; oleaster.

Lit., one who has been reconcentrated; specif., in Cuba, thePhilippines, etc., during the revolution of 1895-98, one of the ruralnoncombatants who were concentrated by the military authorities inareas surrounding the fortified towns, and later were reconcentratedin the smaller limits of the towns themselves.
